-## Risks & Mitigations
-
-- **Schema drift.** A single new table (`sfdc_voucher_change_requests`) with two FKs (`vouchers`, `users`); no `ALTER` on the `vouchers` hot table. Low risk.
-- **Auth guard timing leaks.** Use `crypto.timingSafeEqual` and guard against unequal-length buffers; the spec calls this out under Non-Functional Requirements.
-- **Encrypted-env misconfig.** `getDecrypted` returns `''` for plain-text values, which the guard surfaces as a 500 on the first inbound request. See review pointer R10 for the boot-canary follow-up.
-- **Unknown PRID semantics.** Spec defaults to `404`. If business confirms "silent 200" later, only the controller status path needs to change.
-- **Field name collisions / casing.** SFDC sends spaced PascalCase keys (e.g. `"Lead Status"`); the route-scoped pipe deliberately omits `excludeExtraneousValues: true` because the global pipes in `src/main.ts` have already produced a class instance keyed on camelCase by the time this pipe runs (see controller docstring). The `@Expose({ name })` remap is verified by `lead-change-webhook.dto.spec.ts`.
-- **PII / secret leakage in logs.** Never log raw `Authorization` header or full payload; only `PRID`, `voucherId`, `requestId`, and `changedFields`. The full raw payload is persisted on the change-request row instead.
-- **Module cycle risk.** `VoucherForm` already lives in `eoi_manager/voucher_forms`. Use `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([VoucherForm, SfdcVoucherChangeRequest])` directly inside `SfdcModule` — do **not** import `VoucherFormsModule` (which transitively imports `BookingsModule`, etc.) to avoid a new cycle through `SfdcModule`.
-- **Idempotency / dedupe shape.** The unique key on `(prid, normalized_payload_hash, status)` dedupes identical PENDING retries but allows post-review (APPROVED / REJECTED) retries to land as fresh PENDING rows by design (see spec §Endpoint Specification and review pointer R7). If the business wants stricter deduplication, widen the predicate to "most-recent terminal-status row for the same `(prid, hash)`".
-
-## Open Questions to Surface to Reviewer (do not block implementation)
-
-1. Boot-time canary on `getDecrypted` to fail-fast in deploy logs when `SFDC_WEBHOOK_BASIC_USER` / `SFDC_WEBHOOK_BASIC_PASS` are configured as plain-text by mistake (see review pointer R10).
-2. Whether the dedupe predicate should be widened beyond "PENDING-only" once the admin-review flow ships (see review pointer R7).
-3. Whether the `(prid, normalized_payload_hash, status)` unique constraint should be replaced with a regular index + an app-layer SERIALIZABLE pre-check if multi-rejection retry scenarios become real (see review pointer R6).
